The nature and role of social entrepreneurship and innovation in society. Mapping social bottlenecks and creating a business model to create positive changes. Social enterprises in Estonia and elsewhere, their operating models and legal environment. General principles, structure and financing options for preparing a business plan.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Upon completion of the course, the learner has acquired basic knowledge of the nature of social entrepreneurship and innovation and is ready to use innovative approaches to solve the social problems of society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1)	understands the nature of social entrepreneurship and innovation and its role in society; 2) knows the specific features of the legal environment of social entrepreneurship; 3) analyzes the operating and business models of social entrepreneurship; 4) has basic knowledge of preparing a business plan; 5) knows the principles of social impact assessment; 6) defines indicators for measuring social impact.
